ProtoResult:
. "If $z^n = 1$, then the $n$th roots of unity are \[ z = \cis
   ( \frac{2 k \pi}{n } ), \] where $k = 0, 1, \ldots, n-1$. 
   Furthermore, the $n$th roots of unity form a cyclic subgroup
   of\/ ${\mathbb T}$ of order $n$."
